name: The Temptation Dabolim - 24x7 Complete Food Shop

reviews.review_text:
Temptation is my last-minute go-to place for a range of cravings. Located on the Vasco-Verna/Airport road, it’s an affordable and convenient stop for a quick bite. I’ve been here multiple times, and while the pricing is reasonable, the food quality matches what you pay for. It’s not the most delicious out there, but it’s decent, with consistency at a good 80-90% of the time.

Speaking specifically about this outlet, the staff experience is mixed—50% are diligent and maintain hygiene, while the other 50% seem indifferent, either bored or working just for the paycheck. You can tell from their demeanor and lack of attention to cleanliness. Management should take this seriously, as this outlet has potential, but a few careless staff members could tarnish the brand’s reputation.

I’ve noticed unclean tables and cockroaches on multiple occasions(Top Section), and poor hygiene practices among some kitchen staff. This needs urgent attention to improve the overall experience.

If you want to experience the best of Temptation, I’d recommend visiting their Margao store instead.

A short walk from the airport,

Delicious food at affordable prices, if you have some time to kill at the airport then I would definitely recommend this place.

All items are priced reasonably. They have baguettes, soft rolls, sandwiches,cheesecakes, cakes ,snacks , coffee,tea..etc...all priced between 20-200

From the sitting area you can spot Indian Air force jets, helicopters.

Visited twice, tried cinnamon carrot cake and blueberry cheesecake. Both excellent and delicious and just the right amount pf sweet. Pleasantly surprised with the place.

They don't have a lot of coffee options (like cappuccino etc) just basic machine coffee (even cold coffee is from a dispenser) but it's decent.

description:
**A Review of The Temptation Dabolim – 24x7 Complete Food Shop**

Nestled conveniently near the airport in Dabolim, The Temptation Dabolim has earned a solid rating of 4.1 based on 812 reviews, positioning it as a popular destination for travelers and locals alike. This 24-hour food shop is a haven for those seeking comfort food at affordable prices, evident from the recurring mention of their broad selection, including bakery items, quick snacks, and hearty meals. However, the tag cloud reveals some concerns, particularly regarding hygiene, as "cockroach" and "hygiene" both frequently appear in customer feedback.

**Ambiance & Design**

Upon entering The Temptation, one is greeted by an ambiance that blends a casual diner feel with a practical design. The photographs showcase a clean yet simple interior, with brightly lit seating areas that offer a view of the bustling airport surroundings, including glimpses of Indian Air Force jets and helicopters. The practical seating arrangements are ideal for quick bites, while the inviting display of baked goods—reflected beautifully in the images—adds to the allure. Despite the modest decor, the vibrancy of activity gives life to the space, making it a lively stop for travelers with a moment to spare.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at The Temptation is a delightful exploration of budget-friendly options, interpreting comfort food through an array of dishes. With items priced reasonably between 20-200, patrons have an exciting selection that includes sandwiches, baguettes, soft rolls, and a dessert section featuring mouth-watering offerings like cinnamon carrot cake and blueberry cheesecake. The desserts, particularly acclaimed in reviews for their perfect sweetness, encourage guests to indulge. However, it is worth noting the feedback regarding their coffee choices; while the basic machine coffee suffices for many, those desiring a more robust coffee experience may find limitations.

The visual beauty of the food is also commendable. Customers have documented their delightful treats, showcasing cakes and fresh sandwiches that not only tantalize the taste buds but also present a feast for the eyes—perfectly capturing the essence of quick yet satisfying dining.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Customer experiences at The Temptation Dabolim appear to be varied. While several guests highlight affordability and overall decent food quality, the reviews spotlight a concerning inconsistency in service and hygiene. Some staff are noted for their diligence and attentiveness, while others were described as indifferent, leading to lapses in cleanliness and attention, particularly at times when patrons observed unclean tables and pest issues. Management is urged to prioritize staff training and hygiene practices to enhance the dining experience and restore confidence among diners.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz around The Temptation has been a mixed bag; social media and review platforms reveal a loyal customer base enamored by its convenience and reliable fare. Nonetheless, the persistent negative remarks concerning hygiene and service quality underscore a need for improvement. Despite the drawbacks, customers appreciate this eatery's role as a go-to spot for quick, satisfying meals before or after flights.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The provided images beautifully illustrate both the inviting ambiance and the appetizing food offerings at The Temptation. Pictures of delectable cakes and well-assembled sandwiches showcase the culinary care put into the menu, even as they may occasionally reflect the challenges faced by the establishment regarding cleanliness. These visuals serve to entice first-time visitors while also highlighting areas needing improvement.

In conclusion, The Temptation Dabolim stands out for its convenient location, extensive menu, and budget-friendly pricing, yet it faces challenges with service and hygiene that demand attention. Potential visitors are encouraged to enjoy its offerings while hoping for a focus on customer service enhancements in the future.
